  "body": "Most of my react methods start with \"var self = this, ...\". A small but very sweet feature would be to pass \"this\" as the first parameter. As far as I know, this wouldn't be breakable change because most methods don't take any parameters.\n\nSo, instead of:\n\n```\nvar MehComponent = React.createClass({\n  componentWillMount: function() {\n    var self = this;\n\n    some_stuff(function() {\n      self...\n    });\n  },\n\n  render: function() {\n   var self = this;\n\n    some_stuff(function() {\n      self...\n    });\n  }\n});\n```\n\nIt would become:\n\n```\nvar MehComponent = React.createClass({\n  componentWillMount: function(self) {\n    some_stuff(function() {\n      self...\n    });\n  },\n\n  render: function(self) {\n    some_stuff(function() {\n      self...\n    });\n  }\n});\n```\n",
